            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In the 1970s, Lisp and APL REPLs represented something we’ve lost: true interactive, exploratory programming environments where developer feedback was instantaneous, context was persistent, and the entire system was designed around the developer’s cognitive workflow.\n...\nFor decades, programming languages have tried to optimize for both development and production simultaneously, a conflation that created unnecessary complexity.\n..."
