    "client_msg_id": "0427da9d-0b21-401d-93b3-315e5e0ebeff",
    "text": "This loss is one of my topics in <https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3689492.3689808|Redressing the Balance: A Yin-Yang Perspective on Information Technology>. It's sad to look back at 30 years of working in computational science and noting that my (almost) first environment, APL, was the best I ever had in terms of being made for the work I do.\n\n\"Almost\" because my very first programming environment was BASIC on a TRS-80. I learned APL (initially on an IBM mainframe) a year later.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
